## Project Structure (canonical reference)

The layout below is the **single source of truth** for where code lives. Follow it for every new file or package.

- When adding new packages, directories, or layers, place them according to this structure.
- If the codebase has already diverged from this layout, or you are introducing a new structural element (e.g. a new top-level area), **update this rule** so the "Project Structure" section reflects the current or new layout. The rule must stay in sync with the project so it remains the canonical reference.
- You do not need to "review" structure on every change — only follow it, and when you change the layout, update this rule.

```
/
├── doc/                         # LINHA CENTRAL
│   ├── 00-INDEX.md              # Vitrine (ler primeiro)
│   ├── backlog/                 # B001, B002, … — 1 arquivo por fix pequeno
│   ├── specs/                   # 0001, 0002, … — features grandes
│   ├── epics/                   # E001, … — análises longas
│   └── adr/                     # Architecture Decision Records
├── docs/                        # Runbooks (deploy, backup, integrações)
├── cmd/
│   └── api/
│       └── main.go              # Entry point only — wires deps
├── internal/
│   ├── handler/                 # HTTP handlers (thin, no business logic)
│   ├── service/                 # Business logic layer
│   ├── repository/              # DB access only — no HTTP knowledge
│   ├── model/                   # Shared domain structs
│   └── middleware/              # Auth, logging, recovery
├── pkg/                         # Reusable, non-domain packages
├── migrations/                  # SQL migration files
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   └── app/
│   │       ├── core/            # Singleton services, interceptors, guards, shell auth
│   │       ├── shared/          # Presentational components, pipes, directives
│   │       ├── features/        # Feature routes, smart + dumb components, feature services
│   │       └── layouts/         # Dashboard shell, nav, page wrappers
│   └── ...
├── .cursor/                     # Cursor agents, rules, skills
└── docker-compose.yml
```

