## API Design Rules

- Every endpoint follows `/{version}/{resource}` — e.g. `/v1/reports`
- Responses are always JSON with a consistent envelope:
  ```json
  { "data": <T>, "error": null, "meta": { "page": 1, "total": 100 } }
  ```
- Errors follow RFC 7807 Problem Details:
  ```json
  { "type": "/errors/not-found", "title": "Resource not found", "status": 404, "detail": "..." }
  ```
- Never expose internal IDs, stack traces, or raw DB errors to the client
- All timestamps are UTC ISO 8601 strings

